  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Hospitals are legally mandated to secure identifiable patient data, especially when shared with third-party AI vendors 42.",
    "However, integrating LLMs into healthcare systems introduces risks such as prompt injection attacks, where malicious actors manipulate the AI's behavior, data memorization, which risks retention of sensitive information, and arbitrary code execution.",
    "While ongoing research addresses these risks through enhanced red-teaming practices and guardrail standardization 43, 44, these solutions are still in early stages and are not yet fully operational or widely implemented 45.",
    "A significant gap in the current landscape is the lack of rigorous review of FDA-approved medical algorithms post-deployment, which should engage clinicians, ethicists, patients, and caregivers.",
    "Fewer than 30% of AI tools have had their performance and effectiveness thoroughly scrutinized 46, 47."
  ],
